{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620492","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620492"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:43:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:43:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16628"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16628","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16628"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.53,0.1,0.03,0.03,0.3]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9319"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76677"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9319","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9319"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16628"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62174"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5307"},{"type":"tags","id":"7026"},{"type":"tags","id":"8503"},{"type":"tags","id":"10146"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22092"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22787"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76677","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76677"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe progesterone-only contraceptive pill is an effective form of hormonal contraception that contains synthetic progestogens without oestrogen.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary mechanism of action of the progesterone-only contraceptive pill?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Thickens cervical mucus","Prevents follicular development","Induces endometrial shedding","Prevents corpus luteum formation","Blocks luteinising hormone surge"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary mechanism of action of the progesterone-only pill is \u003Cstrong\u003Ethickening of cervical mucus\u003C/strong\u003E, which creates a barrier that prevents sperm penetration. This effect occurs maximally at 2-3 hours post ingestion and is the most reliable and consistent mechanism of action. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInduces endometrial shedding\u003C/strong\u003E - The progesterone-only pill thins the endometrium as a secondary contraceptive mechanism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents corpus luteum formation\u003C/strong\u003E - as ovulations still occurs in about 50% of patients, this is not a primary mechanism. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks luteinising hormone surge\u003C/strong\u003E - although this may occur, again as ovulations still occurs in about 50% of patients, this is not a primary mechanism. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents follicular development\u003C/strong\u003E - While some follicular development suppression occurs, this is not consistent enough to be the primary mechanism of action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Progesterone-only contraceptive pills work primarily by thickening cervical mucus to prevent sperm penetration.","Progesterone-only pills suppress ovulation in approximately half of patients","Progesterone-only pills thin the endometrium as a secondary mechanism of action, make it less suitable for implantation."],"references":["Therapeutic Guideli